![critical](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/critical.svg)

This implementation has a critical bug that breaks transaction atomicity. The call to `user.generatePasswordResetToken()` does not pass the `session`, so the `save()` operation within that method happens outside the transaction.

Additionally, since `generatePasswordResetToken` already saves the user, the call to `saveUserSafelyWithSession` is redundant and should be removed.

To fix this, pass the session to `generatePasswordResetToken` and remove the redundant save.

```suggestion
        if (user && typeof user.generatePasswordResetToken === 'function') {
          resetToken = await user.generatePasswordResetToken({ session });
        }
        return resetToken;
```

