![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

The `isTransactionSupported` method performs a database operation every time it's called. Since transaction support for a given database deployment doesn't change during runtime, you can cache this result in the `_supportsTransactions` static property to avoid repeated, unnecessary database checks and improve performance.

```typescript
  static async isTransactionSupported(): Promise<boolean> {
    if (typeof this._supportsTransactions === 'boolean') {
      return this._supportsTransactions;
    }

    try {
      await connectToDatabase();

      // Try to start a session to test transaction support
      const session = await mongoose.startSession();
      try {
        // Attempt to start a transaction
        session.startTransaction();
        await session.commitTransaction();
        this._supportsTransactions = true;
      } catch {
        // Transactions not supported (standalone MongoDB instance)
        this._supportsTransactions = false;
      } finally {
        await session.endSession();
      }
    } catch (error) {
      console.warn('Unable to check transaction support:', error);
      this._supportsTransactions = false;
    }
    return this._supportsTransactions;
  }
```

